Prime Minister Matteo Renzi of Italy will visit the White House for an Official Visit on October 18, 2016. The visit is an opportunity to celebrate the strong relationship between the United States and Italy and discuss the future of Europe. The two countries cooperate on various issues such as climate change, the global refugee crisis, global security, and inclusive economic growth. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama will host Prime Minister Renzi and his wife, Mrs. Agnese Landini, for a State Dinner on the evening of October 18.